**Functional Interface**
Java mainly enable backward compatibility so that they manage a way that refers
previous concept of java.

So Lambda expression refers mainly interface or spacial kind of interface
that is known as Functional interface.
"So A Lambda Expression type is a interface" which is Functional interface
Characteristics of Functional interface
1/ No special syntax/keyword for lambdas
2/Can treat it just like any other interface
3/ ....but a special sybtype
4/ but with a rule
---A functional interface need to have a Single Abstract Method(SAM)

***
Though Functional interface need to have a single abstract method,what happen
if anyone add one extra method to it. to prevent this error we have method level annotation @FunctionalInterface
it's shows error to add extra method which is a functional interface.